295
00:15:29,386 --> 00:15:30,387
<i>♪ And eat them both up ♪</i>

296
00:15:30,471 --> 00:15:33,891
<i>♪ You put the Peeps in the chili pot</i>
<i>And add the M&amp;M's ♪</i>

297
00:15:33,974 --> 00:15:38,687
<i>♪ You put the Peeps in the chili pot</i>
<i>It makes it taste... bad ♪</i>

298
00:15:39,229 --> 00:15:44,818
[clears throat] I'm gonna eat
all this chili and/or die trying.

299
00:15:44,902 --> 00:15:48,697
Anyone want any?
I'm just gonna put it right down here.

300
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:50,699
Come on. Dip your paws in my chili.

301
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:52,701
Scoop your little mittens
right in the stew.

302
00:15:53,202 --> 00:15:55,788
Professor, I can see
that you're going through something,

303
00:15:55,871 --> 00:15:59,583
but exams are next week.
So, can you teach us anything?

304
00:15:59,667 --> 00:16:01,585
All right, nerd.

305
00:16:02,169 --> 00:16:04,713
You want to learn something?
I'll teach you something.

306
00:16:04,797 --> 00:16:06,256
I'm gonna teach you the meaning of life.

307
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:07,883
How do you like them apples?

308
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:12,054
Now, over the last 2,500 years,

309
00:16:12,137 --> 00:16:15,307
Western philosophers
have formed three main theories

310
00:16:15,391 --> 00:16:17,142
on how to live an ethical life.

311
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:19,770
Now, first off, there's "virtue ethics."

312
00:16:19,853 --> 00:16:24,858
Aristotle believed that there were
certain virtues of mind and character,

313
00:16:24,942 --> 00:16:26,610
like courage or generosity,

314
00:16:26,694 --> 00:16:30,698
<i>and you should try to develop yourself</i>
<i>in accordance with those virtues.</i>

315
00:16:30,781 --> 00:16:32,366
The gift will be anonymous.

316
00:16:32,449 --> 00:16:34,576
Next, there's consequentialism.

317
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:38,706
The basis for judgment about
whether something is right or wrong

318
00:16:38,789 --> 00:16:41,750
stems from the consequences
of that action.

319
00:16:41,834 --> 00:16:45,004
<i>How much utility or good</i>
<i>did it accomplish</i>

320
00:16:45,087 --> 00:16:46,839
<i>versus how much pain or bad.</i>

321
00:16:46,922 --> 00:16:49,216
And finally, there's deontology.

322
00:16:49,299 --> 00:16:52,928
The school of thought
that there are strict rules and duties

323
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:55,973
<i>that everyone must adhere to</i>
<i>in a functioning society.</i>

324
00:16:56,056 --> 00:16:59,393
<i>Being ethical is simply identifying</i>
<i>and obeying those duties</i>

325
00:16:59,476 --> 00:17:01,270
<i>and following those rules.</i>

326
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:03,147
But here's the thing,
my little chili babies,

327
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:06,442
all three of those theories
are hot, stinky cat dookie.

328
00:17:06,525 --> 00:17:08,569
The true meaning of life,

329
00:17:09,236 --> 00:17:14,366
the actual ethical system
that you should all follow is nihilism.

330
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:17,786
The world is empty.

331
00:17:17,870 --> 00:17:22,666
There is no point to anything
and you're just gonna die.

332
00:17:23,709 --> 00:17:24,835
So, do whatever!

333
00:17:25,335 --> 00:17:29,757
And now, I'm gonna eat
my marshmallow candy chili in silence,

334
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:33,969
and you all can jump up your own butts.

335
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:36,388
Is that gonna be on the test?

336
00:17:36,472 --> 00:17:38,223
Yes. And no.

337
00:17:38,974 --> 00:17:40,976
And you all get A's or F's.

338
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:43,312
And there is no test,
and you all failed it.

339
00:17:43,395 --> 00:17:45,606
And you all got A's. Who cares?

340
00:17:46,190 --> 00:17:49,276
Goodbye. Goodbye.

341
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:57,159
Cool lecture.

342
00:17:58,118 --> 00:18:00,996
And cooler shirt. You feeling all right?

343
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,873
-Feel fine.
-[Eleanor] Hmm.

344
00:18:02,956 --> 00:18:07,336
I do have a stomachache.
Why do I always have a stomachache?

345
00:18:07,419 --> 00:18:10,047
Well, you just ate 50 pounds
of chili, bro. This one's on you.

346
00:18:10,130 --> 00:18:14,760
Look, I know the future seems bleak,
but I have a plan.

347
00:18:14,843 --> 00:18:15,928
Come with me.

348
00:18:18,597 --> 00:18:20,682
Nah-uh-uh, leave that chili, weirdo.

349
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:27,147
