for cinnamon rolls

353
00:18:34,822 --> 00:18:36,406
made out of pizza dough.

354
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:37,324
-[chuckles]
-[Michael] Ha!

355
00:18:38,534 --> 00:18:41,912
Maybe someone, some day,
can learn from our mistakes

356
00:18:41,995 --> 00:18:46,125
and enact real change
in the process of judging people.

357
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:50,212
But for now, Janet, old friend,

358
00:18:50,295 --> 00:18:54,299
we are going to enjoy our time on Earth
before we're retired.

359
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:56,218
-[Janet] Hmm.
-[Michael] So, let's get started.

360
00:18:56,301 --> 00:18:57,719
I know it's touristy,

361
00:18:57,803 --> 00:19:00,514
but I'd really like to
visit a LensCrafters.

362
00:19:00,597 --> 00:19:02,057
[Janet] Ooh! And I'd like to get bangs.

363
00:19:03,475 --> 00:19:06,854
Hey, guys. It's really nice to see you.

364
00:19:06,937 --> 00:19:11,275
Um, is everything okay? I mean,
other than, you know, everything?

365
00:19:11,358 --> 00:19:16,280
We've started to accept our fates.
It's all chili under the bridge.

366
00:19:17,573 --> 00:19:20,117
Good, you're all here. Big news, everyone.

367
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:22,786
-We got married!
-We got tacos!

368
00:19:23,495 --> 00:19:26,623
Yeah, yeah, we got married.
And then after we got married,

369
00:19:26,707 --> 00:19:28,959
we got tacos!

370
00:19:29,042 --> 00:19:32,546
-Wow! Wow, that's crazy!
-[Michael speaking indistinctly]

371
00:19:32,629 --> 00:19:34,423
Well, it's strictly platonic, of course.

372
00:19:34,506 --> 00:19:38,468
We only did it so I could
legally give Jason half my money.

373
00:19:38,552 --> 00:19:40,888
We just popped over to the British Embassy
